This file exists so wwwroot is always present in a fresh checkout/build - ASP.NET Core's
WebApplication.CreateBuilder() throws a DirectoryNotFoundException from its static web assets
loader if this directory is entirely absent at build time (not just empty), which crashes the app
before it ever reaches a single line of Program.cs. See LocalFileStorageService and Program.cs for
the runtime-side handling of the uploads/ subdirectory.
